# Audio stays OUT of git on purpose.
#
# A stock-music licence (Envato Elements and friends) covers USING a track inside an end product like this
# game. It does not cover redistributing the raw audio on its own — and a public repo does exactly that:
# anyone can clone it, or hit the raw file URL, and walk off with the track.
#
# So: keep your files here to play locally, and to publish them, host them somewhere you control and point
# tracks.js at the URLs instead. See README.md.
*.mp3
*.m4a
*.ogg
*.wav
*.flac
